name: Chris Jensen
text: Promise a lot & deliver very little. Got 5 employees from them said that at least one would speak English fluently, did not get this. Was promised at least one would have a license, again lied to. Then when they refused to go work and I told the owner that I was no longer going to use them, he told me I was in breach of contract! Horable company to be involved with

resp.text: Thank you for sharing a review of your recent experience with Good Labor Jobs. I’m disappointed we did not deliver the outstanding level of service we are known for, and I apologize that this led to an overall poor experience. If you would like to provide further feedback regarding how we can improve our process please contact our office.

name: Brian Bowman
text: Nothing takes 45 minutes to cook. We spent our allotted lunch time waiting for our food while we watched others arrive after us and eat before us, yet we ordered simple dishes from the menu. Two of us got our food to go, so back at work it was lukewarm although somewhat tasty. As two of us left the place with our orders, we realized that our inordinate wait time was possibly because we- 1) had a party of six, 2) weren’t Boricua or 3) I didn’t have a Coqui sitting on my shoulder…I certainly hope it was #1, but I cannot say for certain.
